<title>The<i> |khu</i> or Bushman soup-spoon</title>
<summary><i>The /khu, or Bushman soup spoon. This is a brush of native manufacture, the stem of which is also used to scratch the fire together. By |han≠kass’o (L VIII.-1. 6083 and 6084). </i>The |khu is made by the men who bind together the back hairs of the |gipp (Proteles, or aardwolf). There are also details about the springbok&apos;s &apos;paxwax&apos;, or |kuerri, in this account of the making of the soup spoon. </summary><comments>1) p.6083v: the springbok&apos;s |<i>kuerri,</i> or &apos;paxwax&apos;, is yellow and lies on the bone, 2) see also <i>The !au or shaped rib-bone, used by Bushmen in eating some kinds of food, </i>3) This story is found in Book VIII-1</comments><date>January 1878</date><storypages>6083-6084</storypages><category>Artefact and dress</category><author>|han≠kass'o (Klein Jantje) (VIII)</author><keyword><kw>utensils</kw><subkw>for cooking and eating soup</subkw></keyword>
